***Fast and slow pointers*** [0ms 40.3MB](https://leetcode.com/submissions/detail/750313835/)
Hey there! Just another popular problem - boy, they really into LinkedList problems. Idea is simples - we put the slow pointer in the beginning of the list, and n-1 to right of it we put another (call it slow and fast respectivly). Then traverse until last node for **fast pointer**, then simply delete.  Here goes the code! 
```
public ListNode removeNthFromEnd(ListNode head, int n) {
        ListNode fastPointer = head;
        if (fastPointer.next == null) {
            return null;
        }
        ListNode slowPointer = null;

        for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
            fastPointer = fastPointer.next;
        }

        while (fastPointer.next != null) {
            fastPointer = fastPointer.next;
            if (slowPointer == null) {
                slowPointer = head;
            } else {
                slowPointer = slowPointer.next;
            }
        }

        if (slowPointer == null) {
            return head.next;
        }
        slowPointer.next = slowPointer.next.next;
        return head;
    }
``` 
