solutions.content:
**What does every row of Pascal's traingle represents?**
nth row represent coefficient of (1+x)^n. Let's observe this

0th row: (1+x)^0   = 1                                    = [1]
1st row: (1+x)^1   = 1 + x                              = [1, 1]
2nd row: (1+x)^2  = 1 + 2x + x^2                 = [1, 2, 1]
3rd row: (1+x)^3   = 1 + 3x  + 3x^2 + x^3    = [1, 3, 3, 1]
and so on..
We just need to keep the values in increasing order of their power of x.

**Binomial Theorem**
We can use [binomial theorem](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Binomial_theorem) to calculate (1+x)^n.


![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/9bb0fb39-bb0a-4099-8c55-d055157f324b_1627894981.7081034.png)


We just need to calculate coefficient of above formula from left to right. First value is `1`, and if we compare any two consecutive values, then we can consume some caluclation from last coefficient in building a new coefficient. 

Try to find out that comman value in 2 consecutive coefficient.

**Code:**

```
class Solution {
    public List<Integer> getRow(int n) {
        // nth row will contain n+1 numbers.
        List<Integer> ans = new ArrayList<>(n+1);

		// First number will be always 1
        ans.add(1);

        long lastCoefficient = 1;
        int fact = 1;

		// We have already fixed first number as 1, we need to calculate n more numbers
        for(int i = n; i >=1; i--) {
            lastCoefficient = (lastCoefficient * i)/fact;
            ans.add((int)lastCoefficient);
            fact++;
        }

        return ans;
    }
}
```

