Assume that row numbering starts at 1. This will make calculations easy.

Recurrence relation:
*f(r, c) = f(r-1, c-1) + f(r-1, c)*

Base case:
*f(r, c) = 1* when r == c or when c = 1

We use memoization as we will make same function calls a number of times

```
class Solution:
    def getRow(self, rowIndex: int) -> List[int]:
        rowIndex += 1

        mem = {}

        def getVal(row, col):
            if col == 1 or col == row:
                return 1
            else:
                if (row-1, col-1) not in mem:
                    mem[(row-1, col-1)] = getVal(row-1, col-1)
                v1 = mem[(row-1, col-1)]

                if (row-1, col) not in mem:
                    mem[(row-1, col)] = getVal(row-1, col)
                v2 = mem[(row-1, col)]

                return v1 + v2

        ans = []

        for i in range(1, rowIndex+1):
            ans.append(getVal(rowIndex, i))

        return ans
```

