solutions.content:
According to question , abs(j-i)<=k is given which means it related to fixed sliding window problem.

**why fixed sliding window?**
	Because the value of j-i can not be greater than k and once  we reach j-i=k then we will maintain it.
so our window size is k=j-i

**Why LinkedHashSet?**
Using linkedHashset because we need to maintain the order of the window as well as window does not contain duplicate. If the window contain duplicates we will return TRUE

```
class Solution {
    public boolean containsNearbyDuplicate(int[] nums, int k) {
        int n=nums.length;
        int i=0;
        int j=0;
        LinkedHashSet<Integer> hs=new LinkedHashSet<>();

        while(j<n)
        {
            if(hs.contains(nums[j]))
                return true;
            hs.add(nums[j]);
            if(j-i<k)
                j++;
            else if(j-i==k)
            {
                hs.remove(nums[i]);
                i++;j++;
            }
        }
        return false;
    }
}
```

