solutions.content:
* We are doing a **sliding window** technique, which means that we are making a window the size of `k`, and when a number enters this window we add it to a hashmap, and when a number leaves we remove it from the hashmap
* If nums[i] ever equals to 2, then we return true; otherwise false

```
// Time: O(nums.length)
// Space: O(k)
const containsNearbyDuplicate = (nums, k) => {
    let hash = {};

    for (let i = 0; i <= nums.length - 1; i++) {
        if (i - k > 0) {
            hash[nums[i - k - 1]]--;
        }

        hash[nums[i]] = nums[i] in hash ? hash[nums[i]] + 1 : 1;

        if (hash[nums[i]] === 2) {
            return true;
        }
    }

    return false;
};
```

