# Java
In Java hashMap.put(key,value) method returns the previous value associated with key, or null if there was no mapping for key. (A null return can also indicate that the map previously associated null with key.)

So, we iterate through array and put each element in HashMap (key is current element, value is current index), then we check what method put returns. 
# Go
In Go when you are look up for something in map you get back two parameters value and is this key exist.

So, we iterate through array and try to find is element already present in map. At the end of the loop we put each element in map (key is current element, value is current index).

# Both
We check is previous value from map exist and 
current element - previous value <= k

this is our requirement from task:

```nums[i] == nums[j]``` and ```abs(i - j) <= k```


# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)
