# Approach
The most Naive approach I think is the best solution.
The question is pretty much simple.
All we need to do is to form a hash map and store key value pairs as ```element``` and ```it's index``` respectively in the map.
Now check weather the element is present or not.
```
if(not present){
    insert the key value pairs.
}
else{
    Check the difference between 
    the new index value and the initial index stored.
    if
        difference <= k return true
    else 
        update the index of current element.

}
```
